Mickey Kuhn https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mickey_Kuhn 0 Theodore Matthew Michael Kuhn Jr. (born 21 September 1932), better known as Mickey Kuhn, is an American former child actor who was very famous in Hollywood during the 1930s and 1940s. His most remembered role was in Gone with the Wind (1939), which received widespread critical acclaim. He also appeared in Juarez (1939), A Tree Grows in Brooklyn (1945), Red River (1948), and Broken Arrow (1950).
